From: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Jul 2014 13:13:34 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 003/285] arm: omap2+: select USB_ARCH_HAS_XHCI for am43xx

This SoC has a single xHCI controller, so we should enable this
kernel option in order to use the xHCI HCD.

Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-omap2/Kconfig |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/Kconfig b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/Kconfig
index 46edf2c..7e03aeeb 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-omap2/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-omap2/Kconfig
@@ -94,6 +94,7 @@ config SOC_AM43XX
 	select ARCH_HAS_RESET_CONTROLLER
 	select RESET_TI
 	select ARCH_HAS_OPP
+	select USB_ARCH_HAS_XHCI
 
 config ARCH_OMAP2PLUS
 	bool
